[[Category:Russian nouns]]
===Noun===
'''баба''' (bába) ''f'', бабы (báby) ''pl''

#(''disdainful'') [[woman]], [[countrywoman]]
#*Все бабы — [[дура|дуры]]; все [[мужик|мужики]] — [[сволочь|сволочи]] — ''"Every woman is [[stupid]], every man a [[bastard]]"'' (Russian [[folklore]])
#(''child language'') [[grandma]], [[granny]] (short for [[бабушка]])
#:*Мам, а где баба? — ''Mom, where’s grandma?''
<!--#:*баба-яга (baba-jagá) — ''old [[witch]], [[hag]]'' -->
#(''informal or archaic'') [[old woman]] (short for [[бабушка]])
#*Жили-были дед да баба. — There once lived an old man and his old woman.
#(''obsolete'') [[peasant|peasant’s]] [[wife]], [[peasant woman]]
#(''weak man'') [[milksop]], [[old woman]]
#(''technical'') [[ram]] (of [[pile driver]])
#(''technical'') [[drop weight]]
#(''cooking'') [[baba]] (tall, cylindrical cake)
#*ромовая баба (rómovaja bába) — ''[[rum]] [[baba]], rum cake''
#'''снежная баба''' (snéžnaja bába) — [[snowman]]
#'''каменная баба''' (kámennaja bába) — primitive stone [[statue]]

